    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-02T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d427fn1">Sent to Cairo via military channels. The source
                        text is a paraphrase prepared in the American Legation at Cairo. It is
                        apparently the text as delivered to the President. A slightly variant text
                        was repeated by <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">Steinhardt</persName> to the
                        Department (740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss> 1939/32358).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-02T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 2, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President of Turkey, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inonu</persName>, has
                    agreed to go with the Foreign Minister to Cairo “On condition that as between
                    equals he is being invited to a free discussion and is not merely to be informed
                    of decisions already arrived at in Tehran concerning Turkey.”</p>
                <p>The British Ambassador to Turkey, <persName corresp="#p_KHSH1"
                        >Knatchbull-Hugessen</persName>, has telegraphed for authority to give
                        <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inonu</persName> the assurance he desires. It
                    will be possible if the necessary authority is received before the morning of
                    Friday December 3 for us to arrive in Adana by train on the morning of December
                    4 and to be in Cairo about 1 p.m. on the same day by special planes sent for us.
                    At the moment, as near as I can estimate, the entire party will consist of about
                    thirty people.</p>
                <p>All is going along well.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
